	"readme": "# @fluixi-css/postcss\n\nPostCSS plugin for [Fluixi CSS](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@fluixi-css/core).\nA CSS file containing the `@fluixi` marker is processed by the engine: your\nauthor CSS passes through, the `@theme` / `@utility` / `@custom-variant` /\n`@source` directives are consumed, and `@fluixi;` is replaced by the generated\ntokens + utilities. Files matched by `@source` are reported as PostCSS\ndependencies for watch mode.\n\n```bash\nnpm install -D @fluixi-css/postcss @fluixi-css/core postcss\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```js\n// postcss.config.js\nmodule.exports = {\n  plugins: [require('@fluixi-css/postcss')()],\n};\n```\n\n```css\n/* app.css */\n@theme { --color-brand: #2563eb; }\n@source \"./src/**/*.{html,tsx}\";\n@fluixi;\n```\n\n## Options\n\n```ts\nfluixi({\n  base?: string;         // base dir for resolving @source globs (default: the CSS file's dir)\n  emitUiTokens?: boolean; // also emit the --flx-ui-* bridge for Fluixi UI\n})\n```\n\n## License\n\nMIT\n",
	"readmeFilename": "README.md",
